is months too old for a dog to go training i have a little west highland terrier puppy dog he is a lovely dog but he likes to bark and pull is months too old to take him training not at all they are a little more cooperative when they're really young think kindergarteners vs teenagers but you can start training at any age i've even trained new things to my elderly dog be patient though terriers are pretty bull headed and it may take a bit longer to get through to him i've had terrier owners want to quit class when their spirited little guys don't catch on right away like the retrievers and herding breeds in class those breeds were meant to work closely with a person terriers are meant to work on their own in a vermin hole tracking and killing things and they have a really independent spirit Dog Working dog Terrier Border Terrier Bull Terrier Kerry Blue Terrier West Highland White Terrier Nintendogs American Pit Bull Terrier Skye Terrier Soft-Coated Wheaten Terrier American Kennel Club Dog training German Shepherd Dog Jack Russell Terrier Yorkshire Terrier Miniature Fox Terrier Mixed-breed dog Staffordshire Bull Terrier Golden Retriever Boston Terrier Fox hunting Airedale Terrier Housebreaking Breed standard Cairn Terrier Dog show Obedience training Companion dog Labrador Retriever Toy Fox Terrier Tenterfield Terrier Fox Terrier Australian Silky Terrier Dog agility Cattle Belgian Shepherd Dog Welsh Terrier Fox Terrier (Smooth) Mastiff Brian Griffin Toy dog Border Collie Tibetan Terrier Our Gang Basset Hound Ferret The Realm of the Elderlings/Characters Australian Cattle Dog Maltese (dog) Flyball Miniature Pinscher United Kennel Club Breed-specific legislation Australian Terrier Breed club Breed registry Fox Terrier (Wire) Dog breed Best of Breed American Bulldog Pekingese Gray Wolf Schutzhund Whippet Sheepdog trial Livestock RuneScape quests Samoyed (dog) Dog breeding USS Sea Dog (SS-401) Police dog Cat American Eskimo Dog Finnish Spitz Portuguese Water Dog Dog intel